My friend Amy was born in 1995. She married Ken, her boyfriend from Tinder. A pastor married them at Rosewood hotel. She honours her parents. She's thankful for what her parents have done for her. Her brother is also a good don while her sis needs to be a better daughter. In the east teachers and parents stress the importance of filial piety which means Chinese parental respect. They teach that you should honour your parents and take care of them. Recently Amy's cousin has stolen her watch. It was a question of honour to tell her about it. My brother felt honour bound to tell her too. Her dad is a man of honour and high integrity. Both of us are kickboxing fans. In march fred will be fighting chris for the honour of his country. Winning the championship is a matter of personal honour, family honour and national honour. Recently his church held a banquet in honour of Fred. Amy asked me if I could do her the honour of accompanying her to the banquet which I did. It was a signal honour to meet fred. Fred said humbly "it's a great honour to have you here Amy" We asked him if he would do us the honour of becoming our kickboxing coach. He said "we'll have to see" A couple of waiters did the honours and greeted the guests at the door. After we sat down Fred asked the waitress "will you do the honours and cut us a piece of chicken?" Fred said to us "I would be honoured if you could come and see my fight in march" We gave him an affirmative response. Last year the chairman told fred "I would be honoured if you attended the hall of fame ceremony" which he did. He was honoured for his performance in his last fight. Besides winning the championship in the fight he was honoured with an award for.excellence in grappling. His great grandfather accepted a commission as a senior officer. He was buried with full military honours. By the way some people bought front row tickets at half price or less due to a computer problem but the company said they would honour these tickets nevertheless which could cost over five hundred thousand dollars in lost earnings. His uncle was broke several years ago as he bet the farm on his company which went bankrupt later. He managed to honour his debts in three years. I've read in the newspapers that some customers were promised to get their money back if they weren't satisfied with the products. Later they found they'd been sold down the river as so far they have been unable to contact the scammer. The swindler didn't honour the contracts. Amy is a rabbit lover. In accordance with animal law in hokkaido if your pet is a social animal you must have at least two of them living together. Most citizens honour it.

replies.msg: My friend Jason was born in 1995. He married Amy recently, his girlfriend from high school. They will be going to Osaka for their honeymoon. They'll be attending a pageant there. I would've thought that Aiko is highly likely to enter thr final round. Jason said too "My bet is Fumi will enter the final round" My friend Alex has got a commission to compose a waltz for the pageant as one if the contestants will be showcasing her waltz dance which we all can't wait to see. I would like to extend my congratulations to him for receiving a commission for a waltz from the pageant since it's a rare opportunity. I too endorse the congratulations to my friend Kawai on having progressed through the preliminary round. She's a contestant in the beauty contest and I won't be surprised if she progresses through the semifinal. I remember a decade ago there was a protest where the protestors clashed with the police in osaka. I saw it on NHK then. I thought the police weren't tough enough. All the riot police were holding a shield in one hand and a nightstick in the other hand. In this way you can't really fight the protestors and arrest them since you have no free hands to grab ahold of them. That's why it took four policemen to catch ahold of one demonstrator. From a fighting standpoint some of the riot police should be holding just a shield, some just a truncheon, the other both. And all of them should be trained on how they fight when they're holding just a baton, holding just a shield and holding both. It was complete chaos. I didn't think osaka had ever been so chaotic before. The police who I wholeheartedly supported only used tear smoke in an attempt to disperse the demonstrators away which was clearly not enough. The police shouldn't have been afraid of being criticized for using excessive force because it was utterly not the case. Firing rubber bullets and bean bags at the protestors was necessary, lawful and appropriate. Those who sabotaged the nearby buildings and the railings should've been put in jail. The train network was paralyzed by the strike for many weeks. The world had brought the city to the edge of a catastrophe. The united states had already imposed trade sanctions on Japan. The then united states president said he would take punitive action against Japan if the police there used excessive force. Japan was.afraid that America would toughen the punitive import duties still further on alcohol food, agricultural products and clothes, and worse still they would convince other nations to impose international economic sanctions. Of course the downside was the costs of the products in America which they imposed punitive import tariffs on would rise still higher. The economic sanctions against Japan wouldn't be dropped until the then United states president's presidency expired a year later. The next day everybody was warned of the danger of violent clashes only to find that it was a false alarm. There were half as many people in the street. However as you kept up with the news and stayed away from places where there were demonstrations it was safe in osaka. On the same day a bus crash killed twenty passengers. Detectives assigned the blame for the accident to a hailstorm. I expressed my condolences to the families of the people who died in the accident- and then a brutal murder took place in the capital. Detectives assigned hatred and jealousy as the motives for the horrendous crime. By the way it's been reported that some iphones particularly iphone seven emit radiation over the legal limit so I suggest using Samsung Note Ten plus instead as it emits the least radiation out of all phones to to date. S Nine plus also has amazingly low radiation.

My friend was born in 1995. Do you believe in horoscope? What zodiac sign are you? To me, the personality description at times seems correct but I don't believe in the foretelling. I'm a Sagittarius. Tell me about the disposition and personality traits that are typical of a Sagittarius. I want to see if they're accurate. Are you into Zen meditation as well? Many people practise it in pursuit of tranquility and happiness. My friend Paul plays the piano and cornet. His cousin will take her grade seven flute exam soon. She wants him to accompany her free of charge. He isn't sure if he should do it but he doesn't want to pull the rug out from under her. My friend Edward has been having a crush on this girl named Jo for seven years. He's still holding out false hope that one day he'll become her boyfriend but Jo has a boyfriend. He's just being a doormat. During their trip to Thailand, he bought her lots of presents and keepsakes and paid for all her meals but at the end he ran out of money so he had to ask her to lend him some money who's now saying he's staying close to her to take advantage of her and her money. They stayed in a twin room which has a pair of twin beds rather than a double bed. She told Edward that she wouldn't sleep with any guy until she was married which we all know isn't true; she sleeps with her real boyfriend daily. Edward knew it wasn't true but didn't mind. She even said to Edward twice that she was a bit attracted to him which gave him false hope. That's why he's still holding out false hope that very soon he'll become her boyfriend. Another girl named Shirley who he fancied took him to a beauty parlour and sold him facial sessions for over twelve thousand dollars. He didn't know he was being taken advantage of until he made his payment on his credit card. As soon as he made the payment Shirley's whole manner changed. Her expression looked immediately different because she got what she wanted already. She pretended to be cute and said "we can do facials together sweetie..." then he got persuaded. He got rejected by so many girls maybe due to the fact that he has no qualifications whatsoever so he ended up working as a security guard in a residential building with little career prospect and he's so thin; 180 centimeters tall but weighs less than 110 pounds. He fancied my sister but she avoided him. He studied higher diploma in Australia but besides IT he failed all exams and failed them again in the resits so he couldn't apply for a student visa again. He ended up working as a security guard in a residential building whose salary is twice thousand dollars a month. Last week he said he wanted to take a shot at the CPA exam and become an accountant with better career prospects. It'll improve his job prospects but the next day he said it'd be a waste of time if he failed it so he gave up. The problem is he doesn't want to step out of his comfort zone; he'd rather be a security guard for the rest of his life. In addition he's extremely thin; he's 180 centimetres tall but weighs less than 110 pounds. I suggested he gain weight but he didn't listen. I tried to encourage him but to no effect. Jo and Shirley must have swept him off his feet many years ago.
